        <abstract> 
<p>In his last letter FM told CD about four flowers of <hi rend="italic">Lagerstroemia</hi> that he had fertilised with the yellow pollen of another variety or species and which had subsequently fallen off. He has now repeated the experiment using the yellow pollen of a different variety and successfully produced good fruit as large as that fertilised with green pollen.</p> 
        </abstract>
